{"lemma":"شَهْرَيْ","slug":"شَهْرَيْ","root":"ش.ه.ر","root_slug":"ش-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَهْر","root":"شهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":21},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n23208"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"month (unit of time)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"new moon (beginning of the lunar month)","examples":[{"text":"شَهْر عَسَل","english":"honeymoon"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread, to make known, to divulge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make well-known, to make famous, to make notorious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to proclaim, to announce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw (a weapon), to unsheathe"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make well-known, to make famous, to make notorious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread, to make known, to divulge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to proclaim, to announce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to defame, to slander, to revile, to pillory, to condemn, to denounce"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَهَرَ (šahara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Semitic *śahr-\nArabic شهر\nInherited from Proto-Semitic *śahr-."},"ipa":["/ʃahr/","/ʃa.ha.ra/","/ʃah.ha.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23208","headword_ar":"شَهْرٌ","root":"$hr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new moon, when it appears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, A, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) so called because of its conspicuousness. (Mgh, Msb.) This is the original signification. (Mgh.) [See the last sentence of this paragraph.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu Al$~ahora","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ الشَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw the new moon of the month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) Hence it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwmuwA Al$~ahora","text_ar":"صُومُوا الشَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fast ye the first day of the lunar month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.) And hence the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~amaA Al$~ahoru tisoEN waEi$oruwna","text_ar":"اـِنَّمَا الشَّهْرُ تِسْعٌ وَعِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning The utility of watching for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the new moon is on the nine and twentieth"},{"kind":"text","text":"night. (L, TA.) [Or the meaning is, that the lunar month is a period of nine and twenty nights.] ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moon when conspicuous, and near to being full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And [A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lunar month;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain well-known number of days:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because made manifest by the moon: (ISd, K:) an arabicized word; or, as some say, Arabic; (Msb;) and so called because of its being manifest: (Msb, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohurN","text_ar":"اَشْهُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwrN","text_ar":"شُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) The following are the modern names of the months: 1."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaraAmu","text_ar":"الحَرَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often added]: 2."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarN","text_ar":"صَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayoru","text_ar":"الخَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often added]: 3."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 4."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyEN AlA=xiru","text_ar":"رَبِيعٌ الا=خِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aAniY","text_ar":"الثَّانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: 5."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaAdaY AlA^uwlaY","text_ar":"جُمَادَى الاُولَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": 6."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jumaAdaY AlA=xirapu","text_ar":"جُمَادَى الا=خِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~aAniyapu","text_ar":"الثَّانِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: 7."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajabN","text_ar":"رَجَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which is often added the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarodu","text_ar":"الفَرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: 8."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEobaAnu","text_ar":"شَعْبَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which we often find the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEaZ~amu","text_ar":"المُعَظَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"added, and sometimes that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ariyfu","text_ar":"الشَّرِيفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: 9."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaDaAnu","text_ar":"رَمَضَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmubaAraku","text_ar":"المُبَارَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is appropriated]: 10."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aw~aAlN","text_ar":"شَوَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almukar~amu","text_ar":"المُكَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is frequently added]: 11."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw AlqaEodapi","text_ar":"ذُو القَعْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and 12."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw AlHij~api","text_ar":"ذُو الحِجَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see the second of the two tables in p. 1254:] and the following are the names by which they were called by the tribe of 'Ád, agreeably with the foregoing numeration: 1."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^otamirN","text_ar":"مُوْتَمِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 2."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAjirN","text_ar":"نَاجِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 3."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaw~aAnN","text_ar":"خَوَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 4."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buS~aAnN","text_ar":"بُصَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: 5."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~aY","text_ar":"رُبَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": 6."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaniynN","text_ar":"حَنِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 7."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 8."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA*ilN","text_ar":"عَاذِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 9."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAtiqN","text_ar":"نَاتِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 10."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEolN","text_ar":"وَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": 11."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waronapu","text_ar":"وَرْنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and 12."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burakN","text_ar":"بُرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buraku","text_ar":"بُرَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?]. (Ibn-El-Kelbee, in TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^otamirN","text_ar":"مُوْتَمِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [But authors differ respecting some of these names, as will be seen in other articles.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ohurN maEoluwmaAtN","text_ar":"اَشْهُرٌ مَعْلُومَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said, in the Kur [ii. 193], to be the period of the pilgrimage, for by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~u","text_ar":"الحَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which immediately precedes, is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotu AlHaj~i","text_ar":"وَقْتُ الحَجِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnu AlHaj~i","text_ar":"زَمَانُ الحَجِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) applies to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Showwál and Dhul-Kaadeh and ten days of Dhu-l-Hijjeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) accord. to Aboo-Haneefeh (Mgh) and most of the learned, part of Dhu-l-Hijjeh being called a month tropically, as is often done by the Arabs in similar cases, relating to time; for ex. when they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotuhu mu*o yawomaAni","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ يَوْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the period of separation having been a day and a part of a day: (Msb:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nine days of Dhu-l-Hijjeh with the night preceding the day of the sacrifice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Esh-Sháfi'ee: (Mgh:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all Dhu-l-Hijjeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Málik: (Mgh, Msb:) [in these two explanations the two months next preceding being meant to be included:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Showwál and Dhu-l- Kaadeh and Dhu-l-Hijjeh and Moharram,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Aboo-'Amr Esh-Shaabee. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A learned man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) [because of his celebrity:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwrN","text_ar":"شُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) ―         -b5-  [And accord. to the K, it signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like of a nail-paring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is app. a mistake, perhaps originating from a mutilated transcript of what here follows:] a poet says, describing camels,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^abodaA^ona mino najodK EalaY viqapK\n                      \n                     \n                        waAl$~ahoru mivolu qulaAmapi AlZ~ufori"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went forth from Nejd in a state of confidence, the new moon being like the nail-paring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["IF","A","Mgh","O","Msb","K","ISd","TA"]}]}}